features: 🔪 Comprehensive Set for Every Kitchen Task: The Wakoli EDIB Damascus Knife Set includes a versatile Santoku knife (total length: 12 inches, blade length: 6.7 inches), a smaller Santoku knife (total length: 9.3 inches, blade length: 5 inches), and a precise office knife (total length: 7.5 inches, blade length: 3.4 inches). Perfect for tackling both small and large culinary tasks, this set is an essential addition to any kitchen.

🔪 Exceptional Sharpness and Durability: Featuring a VG10 steel cutting core, our knives achieve a blade hardness of 60±2 HRC, ensuring lasting sharpness. The blend of advanced heat treatment (over 800°C) and cryogenic tempering with nitrogen (at -150°C) enhances the quality of the steel. Each blade is hand-ground and polished for superior cutting performance.

🔪 Versatile Culinary Applications: Experience unparalleled versatility with our Santoku set of knives. Ideal for slicing, dicing, and mincing, these knives excel in preparing meat, fish, vegetables, and fruit. The unique design combines a sharp edge and a balanced weight, ensuring effortless cuts and superior handling for all your kitchen tasks. Whether you're a professional chef or a home cooking enthusiast, this set provides the essential tools you need to elevate your culinary creations.

🔪 Ergonomically Designed for Comfort: With ergonomically designed pakka wood handles, these knives offer a comfortable, fatigue-free cutting experience. They are ideal for making precise cuts on meat, fish, and vegetables. Their stylish design and excellent craftsmanship also make them a visually appealing addition to your kitchen.

🔪 The Ideal Gift for Culinary Enthusiasts: Presented in a stunning gift box, the Wakoli EDIB Damascus Knife Set makes a thoughtful and luxurious gift for both aspiring and professional chefs. Its elegant presentation and outstanding quality ensure it's a memorable gift for any special occasion.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Wakoli EDIB 3-pc knife set made of Japanese Damascus steel VG-10 with Pakka wood handle in gift box Damascus knives from Wakoli: Art and craftsmanship - Santoku knife, small Santoku knife, Office knife. Our Wakoli Edib Damascus kitchen knives are considered to be among the sharpest knife series in the world. We emphasize the tradition of Japanese blacksmithing and the perfect combination of high-quality raw materials, such as pakka, olive or rosewood for our noble handles. Our different series not only offer the right knife for every taste, but also for every demand. Whether you are a hobby chef or professional - you will be completely delighted with the quality, sharpness and design of our knives!

Kitchen knife in premium wooden gift box Wakoli knives are available in a wide range of variants and sizes, from Office knives to Santoku knives to Chef's knives - by the way, they also come in handy sets of three to six knives! All Wakoli knives are delivered in a high-quality gift box, which is suitable for storage and gift giving.

Wakoli EDIB 3-pc knife set The blade: super sharp and durable The blade of Wakoli Edib Kitchen knives made of Damascus steel hardness (60±2HRC) ensures long-lasting sharpness and effortless cutting. The handle: beautiful and ergonomic The knife handles made of carefully selected pakka wood grants pleasant hand feeling and ergonomic work. The right knife for every kitchen The pakka wood handle ensures timeless elegance and optimal ergonomics. Together with the blade sharpened on both sides, it makes the knife also suitable for left-handers.

The unique structure of the damask blades makes each knife set from the Wakoli Edib collection truly unique. With this handy 3-piece set of Santoku, small Santoku and Office knife you are perfectly equipped for everyday cooking. Whether vegetables, meat, fish or fruit - cutting and peeling is effortless and simply fun! Wakoli Edib Serise small Santoku knife Well balanced with ergonomic handle made of pakkal wood, the small santoku knife of the Wakoli Edib series is comfortable to use. Whether for cutting meat, fish, vegetables or fruit, the small Santoku knife is distinctive for its flexible application capabilities. Wakoli Edib Serise Office knife The Office knife from the series "Wakoli Edib" is particularly well suited for cutting fruit and vegetables. It is small, practical and yet fits very well in the hand. With the small narrow and pointed blade, it is still versatile and is also very popular with professionals for decorative carvings. Wakoli Edib Serise Santoku knife The Santoku knife from the series "Wakoli Edib" is the favorite of many professional chefs, because it fits well in the hand, is perfectly balanced by the weight and can be used flexibly in the kitchen. A true all-rounder, whether for cutting meat, fish or vegetables, the Santoku knife is characterized by its flexible applications.
